<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<FrameLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#F1F6F9"
    tools:context=".fragments.lesson3.OverviewFragment">

    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:overScrollMode="never"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">
        <LinearLayout
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">
            <LinearLayout
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="match_parent"
                android:orientation="vertical">
                <LinearLayout
                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                    android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="match_parent"
                    android:orientation="vertical">
                    <TextView
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                        android:gravity="center_vertical"
                        android:text="Multiplication of Simple Fractions and Mixed Fractions"
                        android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Large"
                        android:textColor="@color/black" />
                    <Button
                        android:id="@+id/btn_tts"
                        android:text="Read Aloud"
                        android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                        android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                        android:drawableStart="@drawable/ic_text_to_speech"
                        android:textAllCaps="false"
                        android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                        android:paddingStart="10dp"
                        android:paddingEnd="20dp"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="48dp" />
                </LinearLayout>
                <TextView
                    android:id="@+id/description_1"
                    android:text="Multiplication is repeated addition. The cross (x) and the dot (.) are the symbols for multiplication. Between these symbols, the x is commonly used in multiplying fractions.\n\nWith the aid of this module you will discover the varied methods in multiplying fractions. There are different ways in finding the product. Whatever method you are going to use, still you will arrive at the same correct answer.\n\nThis module will help you multiply fractions easily. Let us get started! But, you need to review first your previous lesson in order for you to fully understand the lesson in this module."
                    android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                    android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                <ImageView
                    android:id="@+id/example_1"
                    android:src="@drawable/lesson_3_sample_1"
                    android:layout_marginVertical="10dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="100dp"/>
                <TextView
                    android:id="@+id/description_2"
                    android:text="In mathematics, multiplication is the operation of combining two or more quantities to find their total or product. It can be seen as repeated addition, where the same quantity is added multiple times.\n\nThe symbols commonly used to represent multiplication are the cross (×) and the dot (·). In the context of multiplying fractions, the cross symbol (×) is often used.\n\nThis module will guide you through the various methods of multiplying fractions. There are different approaches to finding the product, but regardless of the method you choose, you will always arrive at the correct answer.\n\nBefore diving into this module, it is recommended to review your previous lessons on fractions. Having a solid understanding of the basic concepts and operations involving fractions will enable you to grasp the lessons in this module more effectively.\n\nMultiplying fractions can be made easier by following certain steps and applying appropriate techniques. Some common methods include:\n\nMultiplying Numerators and Denominators:\n\nMultiply the numerators (top numbers) of the fractions together.\nMultiply the denominators (bottom numbers) of the fractions together.\nSimplify the resulting fraction, if possible, by reducing it to its simplest form.\nCross-Multiplication:\n\nWrite the fractions in a diagonal or X shape, with the numerators of one fraction on the opposite denominator.\nMultiply the values diagonally across from each other: numerator of the first fraction with the denominator of the second fraction, and numerator of the second fraction with the denominator of the first fraction.\nSimplify the resulting fraction, if possible.\nUsing Whole Numbers:\n\nConvert any whole numbers to fractions by placing them over a denominator of 1.\nMultiply the fractions following the steps mentioned above.\nIf necessary, simplify the resulting fraction.\n\nBy following these methods and practicing regularly, you will become more comfortable and proficient in multiplying fractions.\n\nRemember, it is crucial to understand the underlying concepts and apply the appropriate techniques to ensure accurate multiplication of fractions. This module aims to provide a comprehensive understanding of multiplying fractions, assisting you in tackling various problem-solving scenarios.\n\n"
                    android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                    android:textColor="@color/black"
                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                    android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
            </LinearLayout>
                <LinearLayout
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:padding="16dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                    <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                        app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                        app:cardElevation="0dp"
                        app:cardBackgroundColor="#ffffff"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="match_parent">
                        <LinearLayout
                            android:orientation="vertical"
                            android:background="@drawable/bg_gradient_tutorial"
                            android:layout_width="match_parent"
                            android:layout_height="match_parent">
                            <TextView
                                android:text="Tutorial"
                                android:textSize="18sp"
                                android:paddingTop="10dp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:textColor="@color/black"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <TextView
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:textColor="@color/black"
                                android:text="Are you struggling with the numbers mixing in your head? In this tutorial, we will guide you through the step-by-step process of this lesson!"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <Button
                                android:id="@+id/btn_tutorial"
                                android:text="Watch Tutorial"
                                android:textAllCaps="false"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                android:textColor="@color/black"
                                android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                                android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_width="150dp"
                                android:layout_height="48dp"/>
                        </LinearLayout>
                    </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>
                    <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                        app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                        app:cardElevation="0dp"
                        app:cardBackgroundColor="#ffffff"
                        android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                        <LinearLayout
                            android:orientation="vertical"
                            android:background="@drawable/bg_gradient_quiz"
                            android:layout_width="match_parent"
                            android:layout_height="match_parent">
                            <TextView
                                android:text="Quiz"
                                android:textSize="18sp"
                                android:paddingTop="10dp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:textColor="@color/white"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <LinearLayout
                                android:orientation="horizontal"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                <ImageView
                                    android:layout_gravity="center"
                                    android:background="@drawable/bg_list"
                                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                <LinearLayout
                                    android:orientation="vertical"
                                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="10"
                                        android:textSize="18sp"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="Multiple Choice Questions"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                </LinearLayout>
                            </LinearLayout>
                            <LinearLayout
                                android:orientation="horizontal"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                <ImageView
                                    android:layout_gravity="center"
                                    android:background="@drawable/bg_clock"
                                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                <LinearLayout
                                    android:orientation="vertical"
                                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="2 mins"
                                        android:textSize="18sp"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="Per Questions"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                </LinearLayout>
                            </LinearLayout>
                            <LinearLayout
                                android:orientation="horizontal"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                <ImageView
                                    android:layout_gravity="center"
                                    android:background="@drawable/bg_trophy"
                                    android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                <LinearLayout
                                    android:orientation="vertical"
                                    android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="50%"
                                        android:textSize="18sp"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_bold"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                    <TextView
                                        android:text="To Passed the Quiz"
                                        android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                        android:textColor="@color/white"
                                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                                </LinearLayout>
                            </LinearLayout>
                            <TextView
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:text="Let's measure your problem-solving skills to assess your level of understanding."
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                android:textColor="@color/white"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <Button
                                android:id="@+id/btn_start_quiz"
                                android:text="Start Quiz!"
                                android:textAllCaps="false"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/geologica_regular"
                                android:textColor="@color/white"
                                android:background="@drawable/btn_primary_button"
                                android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_width="150dp"
                                android:layout_height="48dp"/>
                        </LinearLayout>
                    </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>
                </LinearLayout>

        </LinearLayout>
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
</FrameLayout>